# TypeScript: Prefer Type-Only Imports

1. Use `import type` for importing types to improve clarity and enable faster builds.
2. This helps tools and bundlers optimize code and avoid unnecessary imports at runtime.
```

```typescript
// Good
import type { User } from './types';

// Bad
import { User } from './types';
```
